**THE OPPORTUNITY**


The Queens Community Justice Center-The Rockaways is seeking a Program Coordinator for its Arches Program. Reporting to the Project Director, the Program Coordinator will manage operations of Arches, a Department of Probation funded, neighborhood-based transformative mentoring services program for young adults on probation between the ages of 16 and 24 who reside in or adjacent to Far Rockaway, Queens.

**Responsibilities include but are not limited to:**

* Serve as the primary point of contact between the QCJC-TR and DOP program staff and probation officers;
* Provide supervision to the team of five mentors;
* Work with probation officers and mentors to ensure effective delivery of services to participants;
* Participate in DOP citywide Arches Project Coordinator meetings;
* Perform strength-based intakes with participants and match them with mentors;
* Oversee the accurate and timely collection and maintenance of participant data and submission of reports to DOP;
* Support the mentors and probation officers in providing wrap-around support and case management referrals to all participants;
* Assist in facilitating group sessions when deemed necessary;
* Build and maintain relationships with local service providers and program partners, including community-based organizations to identify neighborhood resources;
* Attending community meetings and events and other partner meetings, as requested;
* Other relevant duties and activities as needed.

**Position Type:** Full-time, some nights and weekends when needed,

**Position Location:** Far Rockaway, Queens

**Qualifications:** The ideal candidate will have a bachelor's degree with a minimum of three years of experience and experience with program planning and development OR a total of five years of experience as mentioned above. The program coordinator will be required to have strong team skills, problem solving abilities, excellent written and verbal communication, and an ability to work in a fast-paced, multi-disciplinary environment. The coordinator should be able to maintain strong relationships with multiple agencies and organizations both onsite and in the community. Demonstrated ability to work in a culturally competent manner that is responsive to the needs of urban youth required. Prior experience with motivational interviewing, positive youth development, and cognitive behavioral therapies is preferred. Program coordinator must be proficient in Microsoft and Google Suites, Microsoft Teams, and Zoom. Experience utilizing CRM or case management software is preferred. Individuals directly impacted by the criminal legal system are highly encouraged to apply for this position. Additional preferred qualities for these positions include deep connection with the Far Rockaway, Queens community they will be serving and ability to speak Spanish.

